  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions and certain businesses are typically required to:\n\n1. Establish procedures to detect and report suspicious activities\n2. File Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs) with relevant authorities\n3. Conduct customer due diligence and know-your-customer checks\n4. Maintain transaction records\n5. Train employees to recognize potential money laundering indicators\n\nSpecific requirements vary by jurisdiction, but generally aim to prevent financial crimes.",
